The paper deals with the use of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) for search and rescue missions and surveillance, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed algorithm uses partially observable Markov decision processes (POMDPs) to handle uncertainty and errors in observations and motion, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of cameras for detection and target search suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with real-time decision making, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of offline simulations and learning a policy suggests machine learning (cs.LG) as another possible sub-category.
